00:12:04.670 --> 00:12:08.840
Which of the following is not
a valid essential element for a

00:12:08.840 --> 00:12:11.120
contract to be legally enforceable?

00:12:11.364 --> 00:12:17.064
As per the Indian Contract Act
1872 A lawful consideration.

00:12:17.425 --> 00:12:24.084
B. Free consent of parties C Agreement
made by a minor D lawful object.

00:12:24.505 --> 00:12:26.949
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:12:28.590 --> 00:12:33.900
The question is asking, what is not an
essential element for a valid contract?

00:12:34.290 --> 00:12:38.100
So three of these are essential
and one is a deal breaker.

00:12:38.490 --> 00:12:42.030
A valid contract needs
lawful consideration, free

00:12:42.030 --> 00:12:44.250
consent, and a lawful object.

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:45.870
These are all essential.

00:12:46.255 --> 00:12:48.655
But what about an agreement with a minor?

00:12:49.045 --> 00:12:53.785
The law says a minor is not
competent to contract and any such

00:12:53.785 --> 00:12:55.705
agreement is void from the start.

00:12:56.095 --> 00:13:01.255
So an agreement made by a minor
is precisely what makes a contract

00:13:01.345 --> 00:13:04.225
unenforceable, not what makes it valid.

00:13:04.585 --> 00:13:07.495
Therefore, option C is
the correct answer here.

